56530.name: Akama
56530.flavorText: "To many of my people, I am known as a traitor... as Illidan's lapdog. I will remain in the shadows, for now... Actually, maybe I'll just remain in the shadows forever."

57195.name: Al'ar
57195.text: Deathrattle: Summon a 0/3 Ashes of Al'ar that resurrects this minion on your next turn.

56445.name: Aldor Attendant
56445.text: Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of your Librams by (1) this game.
56445.flavorText: Will check to make sure you have a valid libramary card.

56556.name: Aldor Truthseeker
56556.text: Taunt. Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of your Librams by (2) this game.

56524.name: Ambush
56524.text: Secret: After your opponent plays a minion, summon a 2/3 Ambusher with Poisonous.

57217.name: Apexis Blast
57217.text: Deal 5 damage. If your deck has no minions, summon a random 5-Cost minion.
57217.flavorText: Lonely mages can still have a blast!

56461.name: Apexis Smuggler
56461.text: After you play a Secret, Discover a spell.
56461.flavorText: "S-secrets? I don't have any! Whoa, look, a spell!"

56623.name: Apotheosis
56623.flavorText: Defined as the absolute pinnacle of existence. Plus Lifesteal.

56689.name: Archspore Msshi'fn
56689.flavorText: Brave leader of the Sporeggar. Guided by the philosophy that one should not mssh with matters that are not one's msshiness.

56860.name: Ashtongue Battlelord
56860.flavorText: Demons have destroyed the lives of the Ashtongue draenei. Now he’s got a shoulder-axe to grind.

56378.name: Ashtongue Slayer
56378.text: Battlecry: Give a Stealthed minion +3 Attack and Immune this turn.
56378.flavorText: Her other hand attachments include a corkscrew and a bottle opener.

56717.name: Astromancer Solarian
56717.text: Spell Damage +1 Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Solarian Prime' into your deck.
56717.flavorText: Loyal to Kael'thas Sunstrider, this blood elf mage sought arcane power in the Void. Did she find it... or did IT find her?

56398.name: Augmented Porcupine
56398.text: Deathrattle: Deal this minion's Attack damage randomly split among all enemies.

57145.name: Bamboozle
57145.text: Secret: When one of your minions is attacked, transform it into a random one that costs (3) more.

56758.name: Beastmaster Leoroxx
56758.flavorText: Father of Rexxar, Champion of the Horde, and Flexxar, Champion of the Gym.

56528.name: Blackjack Stunner
56528.text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, return a minion to its owner's hand. It costs (2) more.
56528.flavorText: "I'm about to ruin this 10-cost minion's whole career."

56504.name: Bladestorm
56504.text: Deal 1 damage to all minions. Repeat until one dies.
56504.flavorText: Dear minions: Woosh, woosh, woosh, woosh, woosh. Best regards, Bladestorm

57181.name: Blistering Rot
57181.text: At the end of your turn, summon a Rot with stats equal to this minion's.
57181.flavorText: Known as 'Fel Gel' to the Illidari, it's excellent protection against harsh Draenic sunshine.

56732.name: Bloodboil Brute
56732.text: Rush Costs (1) less for each damaged minion.
56732.flavorText: Call Gurtogg a brute if you like, but no one else cares about the wounded like he does.

56686.name: Bogbeam
56686.text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Costs (0) if you have at least 7 Mana Crystals.
56686.flavorText: Some think the mysterious bright lights in the bog are alien invaders, others think they're just swamp gas. Turns out, it's just druids.

56413.name: Boggspine Knuckles
56413.text: After your hero attacks, transform your minions into random ones that cost (1) more.
56413.flavorText: I would NOT want to put my hand in there. It's... SQUISHY.

56417.name: Bogstrok Clacker
56417.text: Battlecry: Transform adjacent minions into random minions that cost (1) more.
56417.flavorText: This clacker's crackers for hacking slackers into whack attackers.

57175.name: Bonechewer Brawler
57175.text: Taunt Whenever this minion takes damage, gain +2 Attack.
57175.flavorText: When you get this swole, arrows are basically free acupuncture.

56734.name: Bonechewer Raider
56734.text: Battlecry: If there is a damaged minion, gain +1/+1 and Rush.
56734.flavorText: And if that minion has a frisbee, LOOK OUT!

57176.name: Bonechewer Vanguard
57176.text: Taunt Whenever this minion takes damage, gain +2 Attack.
57176.flavorText: She came here to taunt you and chew on bones, and she's all outta bones.

57721.name: Bulwark of Azzinoth
57721.text: Whenever your hero would take damage, this loses 1 Durability instead.
57721.flavorText: This plate turned shield you shall wield, praying its powers fel will serve you well.

57177.name: Burrowing Scorpid
57177.text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage. If that kills the target, gain Stealth.
57177.flavorText: It's a game of hide and go sting.

60280.name: Coilfang Warlord
60280.flavorText: Prepare for the staunch conch launch!

56512.name: Corsair Cache
56512.flavorText: Where's a corsair's favorite place to hide treasure? Under their deck!

58170.name: Crimson Sigil Runner
58170.flavorText: He's not the fastest of the bunch, but he'll take a stab at it anyway.

56379.name: Cursed Vagrant
56379.flavorText: Little did he know… it was really the talbuk leg that was cursed.

56523.name: Darkglare
56523.text: Battlecry: If your hero took damage this turn, refresh 3 Mana Crystals.
56523.flavorText: He's got a dark glare, but he sees crystal clear!

57950.name: Deep Freeze
57950.text: Freeze an enemy. Summon two 3/6 Water Elementals.

56526.name: Dirty Tricks
56526.text: Secret: After your opponent casts a spell, draw 2 cards.
56526.flavorText: "Ahh sand in my eyes! Also, I'm being stabbed."

57188.name: Disguised Wanderer
57188.flavorText: He wanders east... always into the east.

56681.name: Dragonmaw Overseer
56681.text: At the end of your turn, give another friendly minion +2/+2.
56681.flavorText: Ah, the Booterang... nothing cures peon laziness faster.

56632.name: Dragonmaw Sentinel
56632.text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Dragon, gain +1 Attack and Lifesteal.
56632.flavorText: On the side, she's training for the annual Dragonmaw hammer throw tournament.

56516.name: Enhanced Dreadlord
56516.flavorText: Photo actually taken across the street in the reflection of a doorknob.

57184.name: Ethereal Augmerchant
57184.text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it Spell Damage +1.
57184.flavorText: According to him, undamaged minions just spell problems.

56389.name: Evocation
56389.text: Fill your hand with random Mage spells. They are Temporary.
56389.flavorText: You too could be the winner of the national spelling spree!

59864.name: Fel Summoner
59864.text: Deathrattle: Summon a random Demon from your hand.
59864.flavorText: All's well that ends fel when the fel summoner summons well.

56393.name: Felfin Navigator
56393.flavorText: Return my fishes to me, and I myself shall carry you to the gates of Mrrhalla!

56460.name: Font of Power
56460.text: Discover a Mage minion. If your deck has no minions, keep all 3 instead.

57174.name: Frozen Shadoweaver
57174.flavorText: She still wears her Frozen Shadoweave set despite the many, many nerfs. She just can't let it go!

56677.name: Fungal Fortunes
56677.text: Draw 3 cards. Discard any minions drawn.
56677.flavorText: Far superior to a beanstalk boondoggle.

58495.name: Furious Felfin
58495.text: Battlecry: If your hero attacked this turn, gain +1 Attack and Rush.
58495.flavorText: Signature moves include Eye Bream, Feast of Soles, and Metamorphofish.

56678.name: Germination
56678.text: Summon a copy of a friendly minion. Give the copy Taunt.
56678.flavorText: I regret asking how sporelings are made.

56687.name: Glowfly Swarm
56687.text: Summon a 2/2 Glowfly for each spell in your hand.
56687.flavorText: Glowflies are distant relations to spelling bees.

56527.name: Greyheart Sage
56527.text: Battlecry: If you control a Stealthed minion, draw 2 cards.

57182.name: Guardian Augmerchant
57182.text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it Divine Shield.
57182.flavorText: "What doesn't kill you makes me money!"

57546.name: Hand of A'dal
57546.text: Give a minion +2/+1. Draw a card.
57546.flavorText: When it meets the Hand of Gul'dan, they're SHAKING.

56501.name: Hand of Gul'dan
56501.text: When you play or discard this, draw 3 cards.
56501.flavorText: His skull also draws three cards. Imagine how many cards he could draw with HIS ENTIRE BODY!

56483.name: Helboar
56483.text: Deathrattle: Give a random Beast in your hand +1/+1.

59869.name: Immolation Aura
59869.text: Deal 1 damage to all minions twice.
59869.flavorText: If you can't take the heat, stop standing in the fire.

56649.name: Imprisoned Antaen
56649.text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, deal 10 damage randomly split among all enemies.
56649.flavorText: Can I get a pair of size XXXXXL manacles?

56482.name: Imprisoned Felmaw
56482.text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, attack a random enemy.
56482.flavorText: It doesn't care who woke it up, someone's getting bitten.

56508.name: Imprisoned Gan'arg
56508.text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, equip a 3/2 Axe.
56508.flavorText: Factory Direct Fiery War Axe. Please allow two turns for delivery.

56624.name: Imprisoned Homunculus
56624.flavorText: He got a time out for excessive vulgarity.

56387.name: Imprisoned Observer
56387.text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, deal 2 damage to all enemy minions.
56387.flavorText: Currently serving two turns on charges of aggravated minion slaughter.

56676.name: Imprisoned Satyr
56676.text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, reduce the Cost of a random minion in your hand by (5).
56676.flavorText: "C'mon down to Illhoof's bargain bin! When the satyr's free, he'll lower your fee!"

56519.name: Imprisoned Scrap Imp
56519.text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, give all minions in your hand +2/+2.
56519.flavorText: His impish imports imply impressively impetuous impropriety.

56392.name: Imprisoned Sungill
56392.text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, summon two 1/1 Murlocs.
56392.flavorText: Imprisoned for ten thousand years! Not because it's a demon. Because of the dancing.

56820.name: Imprisoned Vilefiend
56820.flavorText: If you do the time, you gotta make up the time.

56385.name: Incanter's Flow
56385.text: Reduce the Cost of spells in your deck by (1).
56385.flavorText: "Gettin' them discounts in bulk amounts, spells can come, and spells can go, castin' costs drop with my sweet, sweet flow."

57191.name: Infectious Sporeling
57191.text: After this damages a minion, turn it into an Infectious Sporeling.
57191.flavorText: "The best thing about being me—there’s so many 'me's."

56684.name: Ironbark
56684.text: Give a minion +1/+3 and Taunt. Costs (0) if you have at least 7 Mana Crystals.
56684.flavorText: "The important thing, son, is to protect your spores! I have spoken!"

56622.name: Kael'thas Sunstrider
56622.text: Every third spell you cast each turn costs (1).
56622.flavorText: “Descent of Dragons was merely a set back!”

56534.name: Kanrethad Ebonlocke
56534.text: Your Demons cost (1) less. Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Kanrethad Prime' into your deck.
56534.flavorText: After Illidan's downfall, Kanrethad formed the Council of the Black Harvest to study Illidan's fel magic. Some say he was... green with envy.

56510.name: Kargath Bladefist
56510.flavorText: He rules the Shattered Hand orc clan with an iron... bladefist.

58202.name: Kayn Sunfury
58202.flavorText: "Armor and heals may slow my zeal, but fel and glaives excite me!"

57326.name: Keli'dan the Breaker
57326.text: Battlecry: Destroy a minion. If drawn this turn, instead destroy all minions except this one.
57326.flavorText: He calms down a lot if you just give him a turn.

57476.name: Lady Liadrin
57476.text: Battlecry: Add a copy of each spell you cast on friendly characters this game to your hand.
57476.flavorText: When it comes to spells, she loves 'em then she librams.

56420.name: Lady Vashj
56420.text: Spell Damage +1 Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Vashj Prime' into your deck.
56420.flavorText: Personal handmaiden to Queen Azshara turned lieutenant to Illidan Stormrage. Also quite the hair sssstylist.

56554.name: Libram of Hope
56554.text: Restore 8 Health. Summon an 8/8 Guardian with Taunt and Divine Shield.
56554.flavorText: "Think you got lethal? Libram of NOPE!"

56394.name: Libram of Justice
56394.text: Equip a 1/4 weapon. Change the Health of all enemy minions to 1.
56394.flavorText: Proper justice. Throw the book at him!

56555.name: Libram of Wisdom
56555.text: Give a minion +1/+1 and "Deathrattle: Add a 'Libram of Wisdom' spell to your hand."
56555.flavorText: The best wisdom is passed on.

58549.name: Magtheridon
58549.text: Dormant. Battlecry: Summon three 1/3 enemy Warders. When they die, destroy all minions and awaken.
58549.flavorText: Came from another world to invade Outland and bend it to his will… only to be overthrown by an elf from another world who invaded Outland and bent it to his will.

57197.name: Maiev Shadowsong
57197.text: Battlecry: Choose a minion. It goes Dormant for 2 turns.
57197.flavorText: Go directly to Demon Jail. Do not attack minions, do not collect mana crystals.

56685.name: Marsh Hydra
56685.text: Rush After this attacks, add a random 8-Cost minion to your hand.
56685.flavorText: Three heads of marsh-mashing, bog-bashing, swamp-stomping fury!

56472.name: Marshspawn
56472.text: Battlecry: If you cast a spell last turn, Discover a spell.
56472.flavorText: Hopes to someday promote to Marshsqueen.

56899.name: Metamorphosis
56899.text: Swap your Hero Power to "Deal 5 damage." After 2 uses, swap it back.
56899.flavorText: As the humble caterpillar becomes a beautiful butterfly, so too does a demon hunter become a hideous mass of writhing destruction and unfettered chaos.

57193.name: Mo'arg Artificer
57193.text: All minions take double damage from spells.

56694.name: Mok'Nathal Lion
56694.text: Rush. Battlecry: Choose a friendly minion. Gain a copy of its Deathrattle.
56694.flavorText: Never underestimate a lioness when her pride is on the line.

56444.name: Murgur Murgurgle
56444.text: Divine Shield Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Murgurgle Prime' into your deck.
56444.flavorText: Murlocs are not native to Outland. When the Sungills arrived, one among them rose to the challenge of this dark world. They call him... Murgurgle. Murgur Murgurgle.

56827.name: Nagrand Slam
56827.text: Summon four 3/5 Clefthoofs that attack random enemies.
56827.flavorText: Come on and slam, and welcome to Nagrand!

56985.name: Netherwalker
56985.flavorText: You got to Nethercrawl before you can Netherwalk.

56386.name: Netherwind Portal
56386.text: Secret: After your opponent casts a spell, summon a random 4-Cost minion.
56386.flavorText: More aromatic than a regular portal.

57190.name: Overconfident Orc
57190.text: Taunt While at full Health, this has +2 Attack.
57190.flavorText: "I am da powerful! You are da poop!"

56680.name: Overgrowth
56680.flavorText: Zangarmarsh: it's a fungal out there!

56484.name: Pack Tactics
56484.text: Secret: When a friendly minion is attacked, summon a 3/3 copy.
56484.flavorText: "Just you wait, I’ll go get on my main!"

58243.name: Pit Commander
58243.text: Taunt At the end of your turn, summon a Demon from your deck.

58455.name: Priestess of Fury
58455.text: At the end of your turn, deal 6 damage randomly split among all enemies.
58455.flavorText: Furious that she only has six warglaives. The Sightless Watcher has eight! The fel is always greener on the other side.

56598.name: Psyche Split
56598.text: Give a minion +1/+2. Summon a copy of it.
56598.flavorText: This is how the arakkoa make friends.

57166.name: Reliquary of Souls
57166.flavorText: These three represent Anger, Desire, and Suffering. Much like raid night guild chat.

56595.name: Renew
56595.flavorText: I am rejuvenated, I am renewed, I am my own nightlight!

57907.name: Replicat-o-tron
57907.text: At the end of your turn, transform a neighbor into a copy of this.
57907.flavorText: According to the Boom Labs sales brochure, it "impractically makes itself!"

57183.name: Rocket Augmerchant
57183.text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it Rush.
57183.flavorText: "Don't worry, this won't hurt me a bit."

57180.name: Ruststeed Raider
57180.flavorText: Three-time winner (and sole survivor) of the Crashes of Outland motocross!

56824.name: Rustsworn Cultist
56824.text: Battlecry: Give your other minions "Deathrattle: Summon a 1/1 Demon."
56824.flavorText: "Rust… I love it. It's all coarse, and rough, and irritating. And it gets everywhere."

56391.name: Rustsworn Initiate
56391.flavorText: The Rusted Legion's training leaves a little to be desired. He hasn't even had a tetanus shot yet!

56703.name: Scavenger's Ingenuity
56703.flavorText: "A beast, barely alive. Gentlemen, we can rebuild it! Make it stronger, faster... spikier."

57192.name: Scavenging Shivarra
57192.text: Battlecry: Deal 6 damage randomly split among all other minions.
57192.flavorText: Say what you want but finding a matching set of six swords takes commitment.

57165.name: Scrap Golem
57165.text: Taunt. Deathrattle: Gain Armor equal to this minion's Attack.

56697.name: Scrap Shot
56697.text: Deal 3 damage. Give a random Beast in your hand +3/+3.
56697.flavorText: Make your foe's armor your fauna's fashion!

56411.name: Serpentshrine Portal
56411.text: Deal 3 damage. Summon a random 3-Cost minion. Overload: (1)
56411.flavorText: This is why you never flush a three-cost minion.

56603.name: Sethekk Veilweaver
56603.text: After you cast a spell on a minion, add a Priest spell to your hand.
56603.flavorText: The Sethekk weren't able to survive this long by being wasteful with their power. Or their wacky hats.

56520.name: Shadow Council
56520.text: Replace your hand with random Demons. Give them +2/+2.
56520.flavorText: Why is everybody in Outland replacing their hands?!

57979.name: Shadowjeweler Hanar
57979.text: After you play a Secret, Discover a Secret from a different class.
57979.flavorText: What is a shadowjeweler? A miserable little pile of secrets.

56471.name: Shattered Rumbler
56471.text: Battlecry: If you cast a spell last turn, deal 2 damage to all other minions.

57688.name: Skeletal Dragon
57688.text: Taunt At the end of your turn, add a Dragon to your hand.
57688.flavorText: I wish to complain about this dragon what I purchased not half an hour ago from this very boutique.

58201.name: Skull of Gul'dan
58201.text: Draw 3 cards. Outcast: Reduce their Cost by (3).
58201.flavorText: A fellow of evil possessed, of most devious shadow. He hath turned on his kin a thousand times, and now, how abhorred in all imagination he is!

57160.name: Soul Mirror
57160.text: Summon copies of enemy minions. They attack their copies.

57187.name: Soulbound Ashtongue
57187.text: Whenever this minion takes damage, also deal that amount to your hero.
57187.flavorText: He claims to be "soulbound," but I just think he's clingy.

58453.name: Spectral Sight
58453.flavorText: "Pick a card, any card! Preferably the left- or right-most card."

56377.name: Spymistress
56377.flavorText: Spies in Outland must blend into the environment. That means hot-pink gear and bright green hair. It’s a weird place.

57718.name: Sword and Board
57718.text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. Gain 2 Armor.
57718.flavorText: Stab and Slab. Charge and Targe. Slash and Bash. You get the idea.

56660.name: Teron Gorefiend
56660.text: Battlecry: Destroy all other friendly minions. Deathrattle: Resummon them with +1/+1.
56660.flavorText: "You’re fine, friendly minions! You're fine! Don’t tell Mom!"

56823.name: Terrorguard Escapee
56823.text: Battlecry: Summon three 1/1 Huntresses for your opponent.
56823.flavorText: Poor guy is terrified, look at his faces.

56511.name: The Dark Portal
56511.text: Draw a minion. If you have at least 8 cards in hand, it costs (5) less.
56511.flavorText: Some say it's the source of Azeroth's greatest problems—aside from the gnomes.

57619.name: The Lurker Below
57619.text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to an enemy minion. If it dies, repeat on one of its neighbors.

56467.name: Torrent
56467.text: Deal 8 damage to a minion. Costs (3) less if you cast a spell last turn.
56467.flavorText: Weeks of underwater cross-training have really built up her fourarms.

56470.name: Totemic Reflection
56470.text: Give a minion +2/+2. If it's a Totem, summon a copy of it.
56470.flavorText: "Upon reflection, I have decided that your board needs more ME."

56443.name: Underlight Angling Rod
56443.text: After your Hero attacks, add a random Murloc to your hand.
56443.flavorText: "I said I wanted the ASHbringer not FISHbringer!"

57149.name: Unstable Felbolt
57149.text: Deal 3 damage to an enemy minion and a random friendly one.
57149.flavorText: Warning! Your minions are seated in the splash zone.

56412.name: Vivid Spores
56412.text: Give your minions "Deathrattle: Resummon this minion."
56412.flavorText: Hey man, I just feel like... death is just a construct of our imaginations, ya know?

56900.name: Warglaives of Azzinoth
56900.text: After attacking a minion, your hero may attack again.
56900.flavorText: The blades glow green from things unseen, dark dreams whirling in the felfire gleam.

56507.name: Warmaul Challenger
56507.text: Battlecry: Choose an enemy minion. Battle it to the death!
56507.flavorText: Old gladiator rules: first one to die loses.

57189.name: Waste Warden
57189.text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to a minion and all others of the same minion type.
57189.flavorText: Recycle that can, or you get the cuffs!

56682.name: Ysiel Windsinger
56682.flavorText: Reach down into your lungs. The wind that resides there is your greatest treasure. It provides the gift of song, which is free. *But not less than (1)

56451.name: Zixor, Apex Predator
56451.flavorText: A living terror. Teleports at will. Feasts on tainted helboar meat. No head scritches unless you're Leoroxx.
